&lt;p&gt;The Research Team Management Series is designed for faculty investigators and PIs who lead research teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This session provides&amp;nbsp;an overview of the fundamentals of putting together&amp;nbsp;an effective&amp;nbsp;and collaborative&amp;nbsp;research&amp;nbsp;team. Participants learn the principles of recruiting, screening&amp;nbsp;and evaluating applicants. Emphasis is placed on&amp;nbsp;assembling&amp;nbsp;effective&amp;nbsp;approaches to building a cohesive and synergistic team, whether they include postdoctoral fellows, research staff, or graduate students.&lt;/p&gt;
