&lt;p&gt;Based on a true story, the 2024 feature film Sing Sing illustrates the life of Divine G (Colman Domingo), imprisoned at Sing Sing for a crime he didn&amp;rsquo;t commit, finds purpose by acting in a theatre group alongside other incarcerated men, including wary newcomer (Clarence Maclin), in this stirring true story of resilience, humanity, and the transformative power of art.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us for a screening of Sing Sing, followed by a panel discussion on the power of education in prisons and the roles colleges and universities can &amp;mdash; and should &amp;mdash; play to address the mass incarceration crisis in the United States.&lt;/p&gt;
