&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mixing with Reaper&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;(Instructor:&amp;nbsp;&amp;Aacute;sa&amp;nbsp;&amp;Oacute;lafsd&amp;oacute;ttir, MFA Sound Art program)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This workshop offers an introduction to mixing using the inexpensive digital audio workstation software Reaper. We will learn about balance, about EQ, compression, panning, and other common effects, and anything that will help you get started on mixing on your own.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More info on Reaper, including info on downloading, is available at:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://urldefense.proofpoint.com/v2/url?u=https-3A__www.reaper.fm_&amp;amp;d=DwMFaQ&amp;amp;c=009klHSCxuh5AI1vNQzSO0KGjl4nbi2Q0M1QLJX9BeE&amp;amp;r=i3V2t7LpN3lwE8kTGNT_KoH5rt6O_3HlcdE_lO-ItxU&amp;amp;m=BlYJtTKHvI4lFT6kxH1k_aIUJJJWAgbJdvSVIKqTionlodBDjdyukLZM_FTpHM84&amp;amp;s=PRKb29D5KQjBVUpT8h0euMt2ckdzNmm5UQ5M-b97wBk&amp;amp;e=" target="_blank"&gt;https://www.reaper.fm/&lt;/a&gt;. Note that a 60-day free trial is available. It is recommended to download the&amp;nbsp;free plugins from Melda Production as well:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://urldefense.proofpoint.com/v2/url?u=https-3A__www.meldaproduction.com_effects_free&amp;amp;d=DwMFaQ&amp;amp;c=009klHSCxuh5AI1vNQzSO0KGjl4nbi2Q0M1QLJX9BeE&amp;amp;r=i3V2t7LpN3lwE8kTGNT_KoH5rt6O_3HlcdE_lO-ItxU&amp;amp;m=BlYJtTKHvI4lFT6kxH1k_aIUJJJWAgbJdvSVIKqTionlodBDjdyukLZM_FTpHM84&amp;amp;s=-tcpP_CzJ_v5g9FDWaPEgoLyA6oNCieDyelwRyzRDaQ&amp;amp;e=" target="_blank"&gt;https://www.meldaproduction.com/effects/free&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No previous experience is required. Participants are encouraged&amp;nbsp;(but not required) to bring their own laptops to the session.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This workshop will be held in the &lt;strong&gt;Seminar Room of the Music &amp;amp; Arts Library, on the 7th floor of Dodge Hall&lt;/strong&gt;. Ask for directions at the circulation desk in the library.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The workshop is open to current Columbia/Barnard students, faculty and staff. Questions? Please contact musiclibrary@columbia.edu.&lt;/p&gt;
